n In this work I of en\nL had to exert all py strength and\nI 4tinariy times have done what two men\nJiroul have been required to do ordi\n3 tt1 v aiarily This straining myself finally\nr j mused a dull aching and lameness\nf j n my back and as time went on it\n1 got from bad to worse Clio aching\no lt t becoming much more severe so bad\ncf i V at times that I could scarcely get\nJ 1 around Then a urinary trouble set\n1n and developed into something so\nt s fv rious the secretions being scalding\ni k vi ana at night annoying breaking my\nAsleep fivo or six times I used yar\nt j ions remedies but got JKtlct relief\nfrom them I read about Doans\nt f Kidney pills and as they were highly\nrecommended I decided to give them\nra tfiai 1 procured a box at J W\nGayles drug store and they helped\nme from the start I continued their\n1 use until i had taken two boxes and\nfi was greatly benefltted in every way\ntff a J I Tnnt a\nI have every confideMet In Doan i\nKidney Pills\nX For sale by all dealers Price 50\nl f cents PosterMilburn Co Buffalo\nL Newt York sole agents for the United\nr states\nI Remember the namoDoans and\nother A\nsbinkono\ni\nI\nA\ntf\nI\nI\nSUNDAY NIGHT SHOOTING\nAbout seven oclock Sunday night\nWilliam McFrier a negro from Mem\nphis Tenn shot Maria Harris a\ncolored girl aged eighteen twice with I\na pistol In a house in Gaines Alleyj\nOne 6f the bullets took effect in tho\nthigh of the girl whllo the other\nfound a lodging in her breast It Is I\nsaid that there was no quarrel preceding\nceding the fight but evidently there 1\nhad been some misunderstanding I\nwhich led up to the action of McFrier I\nAfter firing two shots both of j\nwhich took effect McFrier ran from\nthe alley to Broadway and thence I\ndown that street in the direction of\nthe L N bridge The police were\nnotified of the occurrence but after I\ndiligent search failed to locate the\nguilty party and he la still at large I\nThe woman who was the victim of 1\nthe desperate assault is badly wound I 1\ned and now lies in a precarious condition 1\nI\ndition from the effects\nDuring the time of the building of i c\nthe New Capitol and the Highland I\nRailroad many Tennessee negroes j\nwere employed In their construction\nThese proved tq be fighters when I\nthey came in contact with the home I\ncoons and so many of the latter haye I\nbeen cut and shot by them within 1\nthe last year that the Very mention\nof Tennessee nigger la enough to\nmake the Frankfort blackbirds take\nto the tall and uncut without more\nado\nWHATS IN McCLURES t\nMcClures has gone up in quality r\nas well as in price The needs of 11\nOur Navy by Henry Reuterdahl I\ngives some staggering facts about our J\nbattleships and our preparation for 1\nwar Great American Fortunes I\nby Burton J Hendrick sums up the In\nhistory of the Metropolitan Railway u\nand its effects on the public One V\nMan and His Town by Marlon H\nCarter is an account of a man who\npractically grew a town and gives\nsome new and amusing firsthand\nanecdotes of the greatest American v\nThere is a discussion of the relation p\nof Hypnotism to crime and disease a\nby Professor Munsterberg as well as 0\nmany other articles of absorbing in ot\nt\nterest IJ\nAre you having trouble with your t\nkidneys There are lots of people to t\nday who wonder why they have pains s\nacross the back why they are tired\nand racking in energy and ambition F\nYour kidneys are wrong They need\nrelief without delay Take DeWitts\nKidney and Bladder Pills they are IJ\nfor weak back inflammation of the t\nladder backache and weak kidneys E\nSold by South Co J3\nII\nPRIZE WINNERS IN ROGERS J\nCONTEST t\ni\nThe lucky winners at the contest\nheld by Rogers Bros the large turn\nare dealers were Miss Josephine\nSeverance of East Main street who\nsecured the Junior Buck Range Miss\nHelen Warrick of the South Side\nthe second which called for an All\nwin Doll Gocart and Miss Gretchen\nGlenn of the South Side the third\nand last which consisted of a hand\nsome Teddy Bear The contest was\ncarried out smoothly and without a\nhitch and the Messrs R Rogers\nSons are to be congratulated over the\nsuccessful outcome of the affair\nes1\nCOUNTERFEIT DOLLAR BEING\nC CIRCULATED\nA counterfeit silver dollar bearing\ndate of 1900 is being circulated in\ndifferent parts of the State and many\nof them have been passed In Louis\nvine The imitation is said to be a\npoor one as the alleged dollar has a\ndull appearance gives no ring when\nIt Is sounded on wood and the mill\nlag around the edges is very imper\nfect Local people would do well to\nkeep a lookout for this latest spec\nmen of spurious coIn and carefully\nexamine all coins or this denomina\ntion itendered them a\n\nBUSINESS OUTLOOK GOOD\nHenry Clews the great New York\nfinancial authority Is very optimistic\nover the business outlook of the coun\ntry and among other reasons given\nfor the position he takes declares\nthat the farms are the great source\nof national wealth and that lie crops\nJust harvested are abundant ndof\nexcellent quality Wheat has taken\nan upward turn again and the pros\npoet aro bright for a considerable\nndvauoo In the price of thIs cereal\nwithin a W ISor more\ni\nJ\n4\nt\n1h\nI\nti\n0\nr\nI\nDANGEROUS FIRE SATURDAY\nEVENING\nQuito a dangerous fire was tha t\nWhich occurred In a cottage at the\ncorner of Ann and Blanton streets\nSaturday evening last at nine oclock\nThe cottage was the property of\nTfios Brooks colored and was al\nmost totally destroyed by the fury\nof the destructive element before tho\nblaze was extinguished The fire de\npartment was on hand in good time\nand did excellent work but the delay I\nin turning in the alarm caused theI\nhouse to be almost destroyed when\nthey arrived on the scene i\nThe building was occupied by sove\nI\nral colored families who fortunately\nwere successful in saving all their\nhousehold goods An old and decrep\nid woman who was a tenant in the\nbuilding was only saved from crams\ntheI\nlion by the bravery of Lizzie Brooks\nwife of the owner of the house Mrs\nBrooks was engaged in assisting the\nold woman Rebecca Johnson by\nname in taking a bath when the\nfire broke out and would not leave\nherself until the aged woman was\nrescued She acted in a most unsel\nfish manner under trying circum\nstances and deserves special com\nmendation for her successful efforts\nto save a human life\nPOSTAL HEADQUARTERS\nCHANGED\nCHANGEDr\nThe headquarters of the fifth dis\ntrict of the Postal Telegraph and I\nCable Company has been changed\nnom Louisville to Nashville and\nhereafter the Frankfort offlce of the\nPostal will be required to report to\nthe latter city Manager Jerry Down\nIngls not disturbed over the change\nHe is one of the best telegraphers\nn the business and is deservedly pop\nular alike with the company and its\nmtrons\nAN ENJOYABLE CHRISTMAS\nThe Christmas holiday was obser\nved in a characteristic way by the\npeople of Frankfort on Wednesday\nand everyone appeared to enjoy the\noccasion to the fullest The churches\nif the various denominations were attended\nended by large crowds of worship\npers and there was no untoward disturbance\nurbance throughout the city to mar\nhe celebration of a day which means\nso much to the Christian world\n1 NESSMAN\nRISING YOUNG BUSINESS MAN\napl\nMr Marcus A Jones has been ap\nminted to the position of manager of\nhe large house of Heise Son on\nSt Clair street In place of Mr Geo\n3 Edmonson who has left for nil\nlols to accept a new position Mr\nJones although a young man is well\nup in business affairs and is sure to\nprove a valuable man In his new role I\ne I\nOA WJI OEL x\nBears thelie Kind You Hare Always Bought\nture I\nBadly\nShattered Nerves\nand WeaK Heart\nToo Nervous fo Sleep\nor Rest\nDrMilesHeart Cure and\nNervine Cured Me\nA shattered nervous system nearly always\nleads to some affection of the heart espec\nially where the patients heart is weak from\nhereditary or other Pauses Dt Miles Heart\nCure is not on